<section id="chapter7">
  <h2>7. Navigating Sites</h2>

  <p>Almost every website has a main navigation. Chapter 7 dissects a typical site navigation and explains every part in detail, explaining why certain semantic elements can be useful for screen reader users. You’ll learn how to create responsive navigation with submenus and understand the difference between navigations and menus.</p>
  
